<item>
            <title>[PIG-2717] Tuple field mangled during flattening</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2717</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;1.txt:&lt;br/&gt;
1, 2, 3&lt;br/&gt;
4, 5, 6&lt;br/&gt;
7, 8, 9&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a = load &apos;1.txt&apos; using PigStorage(&apos;,&apos;) as (x:int, y:int, z:int);&lt;br/&gt;
b = foreach a generate TOTUPLE(x, y) as t, z;&lt;br/&gt;
c = group b by t;&lt;br/&gt;
d = foreach c generate flatten(b);&lt;br/&gt;
e = foreach d generate t;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Describing d shows the schema as d: &lt;/p&gt;
{b::t: (x: int,y: int),b::z: int}
&lt;p&gt;However, when dumping d the output is&lt;br/&gt;
(1,3)&lt;br/&gt;
(4,6)&lt;br/&gt;
(7,9)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Describing e shows the schema as e: &lt;/p&gt;
{b::t: (x: int,y: int)}
&lt;p&gt;However, when dumping I got the following error:&lt;br/&gt;
java.lang.ClassCastException: java.lang.Integer cannot be cast to org.apache.pig.data.Tuple&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;RHEL5 (Linux 2.6.18-164.el5 #1 SMP Tue Aug 18 15:51:54 EDT 2009 i686 i686 i386 GNU/Linux)&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
